urls.title: After Considering $1 Billion Price Tag for Ventilators, White House Has Second Thoughts (Published 2020)
urls.description: A deal with General Motors and Ventec Life Systems to produce tens of thousands of the critical lifesaving devices seemed imminent. Then the announcement was pulled back.

text: Trump’s government pulls back from $1 billion coronavirus ventilator deal, expressing concern about the possibility of ordering too many ventilators, leaving them with an expensive surplus https://t.co/HwdnxkgCAh
